<title>USA: Ford files for Hertz initial public offering.</title>
<headline>Ford files for Hertz initial public offering.</headline>
<dateline>DEARBORN, Mich. 1997-02-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ford Motor Co. said Friday its plans to sell less than 20 percent of its Hertz Corp. car rental unit in an initial public offering.</p>
<p>Ford said the offering, which had been long expected, will involve newly issued shares of Hertz common stock. A registration statement for the offering was filed Friday with the Securities and Exchange Commission in Washington.</p>
